job_details.Functieomschrijving:
As a Fullstack Engineer, you'll contribute to building Dataiku DSS core features by joining one of the following themes:
          + Data Preparation : Develop tools for data integration, transformation, and cataloging, as well as Jupyter notebooks, SQL workbenches, and APIs.
               o Add new capabilities for data integration, transformation, and visualization using LLMs
               o Optimize workflows for large-scale datasets and improve database support
               o Strengthen developer tools like Jupyter notebooks and SQL workbenches
               o Tech stack: Java, Python, AngularJS, Angular
          + Data Exploration : elevate our data visualization capabilities with high-performance charting tools and dashboards.
               o Develop new chart types and optimize visualization performance
               o Enhance dash boarding capabilities to deliver fast and flexible experiences
               o Tech stack: React, AngularJS, Angular, D3.js, ECharts, Node.js, Java, Spring
          + AI & Machine Learning : Collaborate on next-gen AI features, from statistics and time series forecasting to LLM inference.
               o Build next-generation features like cross-provider LLM APIs or integration with the latest Machine Learning models
               o Collaborate with research teams on innovative machine learning experiments
               o Tech stack: Python, scikit-learn, TensorFlow, PyTorch , Java, Angular, AngularJS
          + MLOps : Develop back-end capabilities for automating and monitoring ML model lifecycles while supporting cross-functional collaboration.
               o Build tools to automate retraining, monitoring, and deployment of ML models
               o Enhance collaboration features for ML stakeholders
               o Tech stack: Python, Java, Angular, Angular.JS, Kubernetes, Docker
          + Platform : Focus on scaling and securing the platform while improving cloud integrations and supporting a wide array of data sources and engines.
               o Optimize processing engines for scalability and latency
               o Expand capabilities to support new databases and cloud platforms
               o Tech stack: Java, Python, Angular, Kubernetes, Spark, AWS, Azure, GCP
          + AI Governance : Build features for AI compliance, connecting disparate systems and simplifying governance processes.
               o Develop customizable platforms for managing AI compliance and governance
               o Simplify policy enforcement and integration across disparate systems
               o Tech stack: Java, Angular, PostgreSQL
job_details.full_text:
Fullstack Software Engineer

As a Fullstack Engineer, you'll contribute to building Dataiku DSS core features by joining one of the following themes:
          + Data Preparation : Develop tools for data integration, transformation, and cataloging, as well as Jupyter notebooks, SQL workbenches, and APIs.
               o Add new capabilities for data integration, transformation, and visualization using LLMs
               o Optimize workflows for large-scale datasets and improve database support
               o Strengthen developer tools like Jupyter notebooks and SQL workbenches
               o Tech stack: Java, Python, AngularJS, Angular
          + Data Exploration : elevate our data visualization capabilities with high-performance charting tools and dashboards.
               o Develop new chart types and optimize visualization performance
               o Enhance dash boarding capabilities to deliver fast and flexible experiences
               o Tech stack: React, AngularJS, Angular, D3.js, ECharts, Node.js, Java, Spring
          + AI & Machine Learning : Collaborate on next-gen AI features, from statistics and time series forecasting to LLM inference.
               o Build next-generation features like cross-provider LLM APIs or integration with the latest Machine Learning models
               o Collaborate with research teams on innovative machine learning experiments
               o Tech stack: Python, scikit-learn, TensorFlow, PyTorch , Java, Angular, AngularJS
          + MLOps : Develop back-end capabilities for automating and monitoring ML model lifecycles while supporting cross-functional collaboration.
               o Build tools to automate retraining, monitoring, and deployment of ML models
               o Enhance collaboration features for ML stakeholders
               o Tech stack: Python, Java, Angular, Angular.JS, Kubernetes, Docker
          + Platform : Focus on scaling and securing the platform while improving cloud integrations and supporting a wide array of data sources and engines.
               o Optimize processing engines for scalability and latency
               o Expand capabilities to support new databases and cloud platforms
               o Tech stack: Java, Python, Angular, Kubernetes, Spark, AWS, Azure, GCP
          + AI Governance : Build features for AI compliance, connecting disparate systems and simplifying governance processes.
               o Develop customizable platforms for managing AI compliance and governance
               o Simplify policy enforcement and integration across disparate systems
               o Tech stack: Java, Angular, PostgreSQL

profile_classification.rationale: The job description outlines several distinct themes, including Data Preparation, Data Exploration, AI & Machine Learning, MLOps, Platform, and AI Governance. While there are elements related to AI and ML (TASK3), MLOps (TASK5), and Software Development (TASK4), the role is described as a 'Fullstack Software Engineer' and the responsibilities are spread across multiple domains. The core focus appears to be on building features for the Dataiku DSS platform, which involves a broad range of software engineering tasks rather than a specialized focus on predictive modeling (ML Engineer) or generative AI applications (GenAI Engineer). The role also mentions using AI features, but not necessarily building core generative AI models or applications from scratch. Therefore, it is too broad and not a clear fit for the specialized profiles of ML Engineer or GenAI Engineer.
